Consider the following method.

public void numberCheck(int maxNum)

{

int typeA = 0;

int typeB = 0;

int typeC = 0;

for (int k = 1; k <= maxNum; k++)

{

if (k % 2 == 0 && k % 5 == 0)

typeA++;

if (k % 2 == 0)

typeB++;

if (k % 5 == 0)

typeC++;

}

System.out.println(typeA + " " + typeB + " " + typeC);

}

What is printed as a result of the call numberCheck(50) ?
